Full Title: 44th Linguistics Colloquium "Globalization, Intercultural
Communication and Language"

Date: 09-Sep-2009 - 12-Sep-2009
Location: Sofia, Bulgaria 
Contact Person: Maria Grozeva
Meeting Email: lingkoll@nbu.bg
Web Site: http://www.nbu.bg/index.php?l=963 

Linguistic Field(s): Applied Linguistics; Discourse Analysis; Sociolinguistics 

Call Deadline: 30-Apr-2009 

Meeting Description:

44th Linguistics Colloquium "Globalization, intercultural communication and
language"

9 - 12 September,  2009
Sofia, New Bulgarian University
Paper proposals until April, 30th 2009 to lingkoll@nbu.bg
Registration dateline: 10.05.2009 

Call for Papers

The 44th Linguistics Colloquium is to take place at the New Bulgarian
University, Sofia from the 09.09.2009 - 12.09.2009, organized by the Department
for Foreign Languages and Cultures and the Bulgarian Association of Germanists.
We kindly invite participants. The topic of the conference is:
"Globalization, Intercultural Communication and Language"

In accordance with the tradition of the Linguistics Colloquium, the topic is
fairly open, so that participants can report a wide range of research findings. 
In the Parallel sessions contributions from various areas of linguistics are
welcome. The following strands are proposed as foci for parallel sessions:
Language and culture 
Language and society 
Lexical semantics and phraseology 
Text pragmatics 
Multilingualism
Studies in applied linguistics 
Contrastive language studies 

Papers can be submitted in German, English and French. To provide time for
discussion of each paper (approx. 10 minutes), talks should not exceed 20 minutes.

Paper proposals (including a summary of approx. 15 lines) should be sent, via
e-mail by the 30th April 2009 to lingkoll@nbu.bg 
Registration dateline: 10.05.2009



	
