Full Title: Optimizing the Quality Standard in  HE-ESP 
Short Title: QS-HE-ESP 

Date: 08-May-2009 - 08-May-2009
Location: Targu Mures, Romania 
Contact Person: Anisoara Pop
Meeting Email: anisoara_pp@yahoo.com
Web Site: http://www.orizont.net/users/victor/espworkshop 

Linguistic Field(s): Applied Linguistics 

Subject Language(s): English (eng)

Call Deadline: 22-Mar-2009 

Meeting Description:

'Dimitrie Cantemir' University from Targu Mures, Transylvania, Romania, is
pleased to invite you to participate in the international workshop on Optimizing
the Quality Standard in Higher Education ESP (Business English, English for
Tourism, Engineers, Law, Medicine, etc.). 

Call for Papers 

International Workshop: Strategies for Optimizing The Quality Standard in
English for Specific Purposes.  (QS-HE-ESP)

Workshop themes include: ESP Teacher Training, Quality management in ESP,
Programmes for ESP e-learning, Materials development, state of the art
strategies in ESP education, Teaching ESP with the New Technologies, Learner
Autonomy, ESP Research, etc.

Workshop Date: May, 8th, 2009
Venue: Dimitrie Cantemir University, Transylvania, Targu Mures, St. Bodoni
Sandor no.3-5
Deadline for application: March 10th , 2009

The papers will be published in a volume with ISBN.
Extended date for the submission of papers in extension: March 22nd, at midnight
Romanian time (GMT+2H).  Papers submitted after this deadline will not be
included in the volume.
Authors will be notified about acceptance between 23rd- 30th of March. 

Types of Contributions:
1. Attending in person (in presentia):
a) Oral presentation - 15 min
b) Poster presentation (A1 or A0 or in between)
c)Computer-based poster

2. Virtual presentation (in absentia):
If you wish your paper to be published in the Workshop Volume but you are not
able to attend in person, you can register for a "virtual presentation".
Virtual authors should submit their papers for the reviewing process before the
paper submission deadline. After the review process, virtual authors will submit
a Power Point presentation with voice.

Registered virtual authors will receive a copy of the Workshop Proceedings, a
certificate of presentation in absentia and an invoice of the registration fee.
The shipment will be made by post after the workshop date.

Contact: 
Anisoara Pop: anisoara_pp@yahoo.com; pop.anisoara@cantemir.ro
For submission guidelines and updates, please visit the event site regularly:
http://www.orizont.net/users/victor/espworkshop


 





